
{
  "openapi": "3.0.0",
  "info": {
    "version": "1.0.0",
    "title": "DirectIt API",
    "description": "# Introduction\n This API reference provides a reference to integrate your system to the DirectIT system. The API allows you to create, get, and update orders, and handle accounts and other references. \n\nYou can access to API tool for testing [here](https://api.directx.ca/api-docs)\n ## Base URL\nThe base URL for all the API endpoints is `https://api.directx.ca`\n\nFor example\n* `https://api.directx.ca/orders/1000`\n* `https://api.directx.ca/zpl/1000/12345`\n* `https://api.directx.ca/referenceFields/1000` \n\n# Use Case \n ### 1 Register for API Key \n Contact IT Direct to register for an API Key \n ### 2 Get Quote \n Get quote for delivery using [/getQuote](#operation/getQuote)\n ### 3 Execute Quote \n Create an order using [/executeQuote](#operation/executeQuote) after obtaining quoteID from getQuote responses. \n\n After the call, the reponse will return the reference to the order which will be its __jobID__. The jobID is used when making other calls to update or retrieve information for the order. \n ### 4 Print label \n ZPL Label image can be retrieved using the call [/zpl/{account}/{jobID}](#operation/zpl)\n ### 5 Track an order \n Examples of API calls to use are: \n * `https://api.directx.ca/order/{account}/{jobID}` \n * `https://api.directx.ca/barcode/{jobID}`\n * `https://api.directx.ca/orderPhoto/{account}/{jobID}` \n # Sample Code \n ## 1 Register for API Key \n  Contact IT Direct to register for account. \n## 2 Get Quote \n Construct a patch request with the baseURL: `https://api.directx.ca/getQuote`.\n\n In the payload, enter the details of the order. \n```\n{\n  \"pieces\": 1,\n  \"weight\": 1,\n  \"declared_value\": null,\n  \"pickup_datetime\": null,\n  \"reference\": null,\n  \"special_instructions\": null,\n  \"delivery_url\": null,\n  \"delivery_sig_required\": 1,\n  \"description\": \"Envelope\",\n  \"account_email\": \"jillsmith@example.com\",\n  \"client_email\": \"johnsmith@example.com\",\n  \"address\": {\n    \"name\": \"DirectIT Group\",\n    \"suite\": \"Unit 1\",\n    \"address\": \"100 Barclay Parade\",\n    \"city\": \"Calgary\",\n    \"province\": \"Alberta\",\n    \"country\": \"Canada\",\n    \"postal\": \"T2P3E7\",\n    \"latitude\": 0,\n    \"longitude\": 0,\n    \"contactName\": \"John Smith\",\n    \"contactPhone\": \"123-456-7890\"\n  }\n}\n```\n The response will give the different rate choices if shippable. \n ## 3 Execute Quote \n Using the quoteID from getQuote, executing the quote will create an order. \n\n Send a post to url `https://api.directx.ca/executeQuote`. \n\n Enter in the [apiKey](#section/Authentication/Using-your-API-Key) in the header for authentication.\n\nEnter in the payload: \n ```\n{\n  \"quoteID\": \"E8B7B1EC-55B0-4B57-B7F9-E5DC0DE71A97\"\n}\n```\n \n If the order was successfully created, it will return a JSON response with the values: \n```\n{\n    \"companyID\": 1234,\n    \"jobID\": \"12345\",    \"foxJob\": \"1111\",\n    \"email_req\": \"johndoe@example.com\",\n    \"email_addr\": \"johndoe@example.com\",\n    \"ship_addressID\": 10000,\n    \"trackingNumber\": \"1234567890\",\n    \"isEmailSent\": 1,\n    \"result\": \"Finished\",\n    \"returnJobID\": \"54321\",\n    \"returnTrackingNumber\": \"1234554321\",\n    \"returnFoxJob\": \"10007\",\n    \"returnResult\": \"Pending\"\n}\n```\n The jobID reference for this order is `12345`. This value will be used when accessing data for the order.\n  ## 4 Print label \n ZPL Label image can be retrieved using the call [https://api.directx.ca/zpl/{account}/{jobID}](#operation/zpl)\n\n An example of the endpoint is: \n\n `https://api.directx.ca/zpl/1000/12345`\n  ## 5 Track an order \n Examples of API calls to use are: \n * `https://api.directx.ca/order/1000/12345` \n * `https://api.directx.ca/track/12345`\n\n# Authentication\nDirectIT API uses __API Key__ for authorization. This API key is a special token that the client needs to provide when making API calls. The key is sent as a request header under the name __apiKey__.\nWhen authenticating to the DirectIT API, a sso token should be generated uniquely by a __server-side application__ and included as a __apiKey__ in the header of each request.\n## Accessing your API Key\nYou must contact DirectIT for your API Key, which will be associated to your account info.\n## Using you API Key\nYour API Key should be placed in the __header__\nProperty `apiKey` defines the key being used. \n\nIn Curl\n```\ncurl -X GET \"https://api.directx.ca/orders/1000\" -H  \"accept: application/json\" -H  \"apiKey: xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx\"\n```\n\nIn Java:\n```\nxhr.setRequestHeader(\"apiKey\",\"xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx\");\n```\nIn Python:\n```\nheaders = {\n  'apiKey': 'xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx'\n}\n```",
    "x-logo": {
      "url": "https://ship.directx.ca/img/DirectItGroup_logo.png",
      "backgroundColor": "#070707",
      "altText": "West DirectIt API",
      "href": "https://api.directx.ca/api-docs"
    }
  },
